2026-05-16T12:43:58.8632578Z 3: # qpdf bash completion
2026-05-16T12:43:58.8632855Z 3: #
2026-05-16T12:43:58.8633227Z 3: # Most of this logic was generated by Anthropic Claude Opus 4.7. The
2026-05-16T12:43:58.8633762Z 3: # tabular data is automatically generated.
2026-05-16T12:43:58.8634128Z 3: #
2026-05-16T12:43:58.8634508Z 3: # Design note: bash's default COMP_WORDBREAKS contains '=', which makes
2026-05-16T12:43:58.8635356Z 3: # "--opt=<cursor>" awkward — bash thinks the current word is only the text
2026-05-16T12:43:58.8636040Z 3: # after the '='. Rather than fight this with brittle quoting hacks, this
2026-05-16T12:43:58.8636605Z 3: # completion accepts the default bash behavior:
2026-05-16T12:43:58.8637144Z 3: #   * --opt=<TAB>        completes <value> against the option's value set
2026-05-16T12:43:58.8637739Z 3: #   * --opt= <TAB>       (with an inserted space) falls through to bash's
2026-05-16T12:43:58.8638325Z 3: #                        normal positional filename completion, which gets
2026-05-16T12:43:58.8638851Z 3: #                        you $VAR and ~ expansion for free.
2026-05-16T12:43:58.8639406Z 3: # The second form is the intended workaround for filename values in bash;
2026-05-16T12:43:58.8640382Z 3: # zsh handles --opt=<TAB> filename completion natively and is the more
2026-05-16T12:43:58.8641087Z 3: # functional of the two shells.
2026-05-16T12:43:58.8641411Z 3: 
2026-05-16T12:43:58.8641715Z 3: # Per-option attributes, keyed by "<table>.<option>".
2026-05-16T12:43:58.8642153Z 3: # _QPDF_ARITY:  bare | opt | req
2026-05-16T12:43:58.8642591Z 3: # _QPDF_VALUES: "none" | "file" | space-separated choice list
2026-05-16T12:43:58.8643130Z 3: # _QPDF_NEXT:   "" | next-table | "@value" (value-dispatched)
2026-05-16T12:43:58.8643655Z 3: # _QPDF_VNEXT:  "<table>.<option>.<value>" -> next table
2026-05-16T12:43:58.8644178Z 3: declare -gA _QPDF_ARITY _QPDF_VALUES _QPDF_NEXT _QPDF_VNEXT
2026-05-16T12:43:58.8644611Z 3: 
2026-05-16T12:43:58.8644831Z 3: _qpdf_def() {
2026-05-16T12:43:58.8645106Z 3:     _QPDF_ARITY["$1.$2"]=$3
2026-05-16T12:43:58.8645409Z 3:     _QPDF_VALUES["$1.$2"]=$4
2026-05-16T12:43:58.8645736Z 3:     _QPDF_NEXT["$1.$2"]=$5
2026-05-16T12:43:58.8646028Z 3: }
